fields.title: HTML Fundamentals
fields.description: This course is a deep dive into HTML, the standard markup language for documents designed to be displayed in a web browser. Throughout this course, students will learn about the building blocks of websites and web applications. They will understand how to create and structure an HTML document

fields.title: Introduction and Basics
fields.description: This module introduces HTML and covers the basics including syntax, structure, and common tags.

fields.title: Text Formatting and Links
fields.description: This module covers how to format text and create links using HTML.

fields.title: Images and Tables
fields.description: This module focuses on adding images and creating tables in HTML documents.

fields.title: HTML Lists and Forms
fields.description: This module covers how to create various types of lists and forms in HTML.

fields.title: Semantic Elements
fields.description: This module introduces semantic elements in HTML and their importance.

fields.title: Best Practices and SEO
fields.description: This module covers best practices in HTML coding and the basics of SEO.

fields.title: Python Programming Fundamentals
fields.description: This course provides a comprehensive overview of Python, one of the most widely used programming languages in the world. By the end of this course, students will have a solid foundation in Python and will be prepared to tackle more advanced topics and real-world programming challenges.

fields.title: Introduction to Python
fields.description: This module introduces Python, its history, and its applications in the real world. Students will also learn how to set up their Python programming environment.

fields.title: Python Basics
fields.description: In this module, students will learn the basics of Python, including variables, data types, operators, and control structures.

fields.title: Python Data Structures
fields.description: This module covers Python's built-in data structures, such as lists, tuples, sets, and dictionaries. It also introduces concepts like indexing, slicing, and methods associated with these data structures.

fields.title: Python Functions and Modules
fields.description: This module focuses on creating user-defined functions in Python and organizing code into modules and packages.

fields.title: Python Object-Oriented Programming
fields.description: This module introduces the concept of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) in Python. Students will learn about classes, objects, inheritance, and other key OOP concepts.

fields.title: Python Best Practices and Libraries
fields.description: This module covers best practices for Python programming and introduces students to popular Python libraries like NumPy, pandas, and Matplotlib.

fields.title: Employee Management
fields.description: This course provides a comprehensive overview of essential employee management strategies. Students will learn best practices for hiring, training, assessing, and managing a diverse and effective workforce.

fields.title: Employee Recruitment and Hiring
fields.description: This module will provide the tools and strategies needed to successfully source, interview, and onboard new employees.

fields.title: Training and Development
fields.description: This module delves into how to develop an effective training program for employees, ensuring they have the skills and knowledge needed to perform at their best.

fields.title: Performance Management
fields.description: In this module, students will learn about performance management strategies and how to conduct productive performance evaluations.

fields.title: Conflict Resolution
fields.description: This module explores the most effective methods for managing conflict in the workplace.

fields.title: Retaining Employees
fields.description: This module will delve into strategies for retaining high-performing employees and reducing turnover.

fields.title: Introduction to Stock Trading
fields.description: This course provides an introduction to the basics of stock trading. Students will learn about stock markets, trading strategies, risk management, and analysis of stocks. The course is suitable for beginners with no prior knowledge of stock trading.

fields.title: Introduction to Stock Markets
fields.description: This module provides an overview of what stock markets are, their functions, and major stock markets around the world.

fields.title: Basics of Stock Trading
fields.description: This module introduces students to the basic principles and strategies of stock trading.

fields.title: Risk Management in Stock Trading
fields.description: This module provides insights into risk management strategies for stock trading.

fields.title: Fundamental Analysis
fields.description: This module teaches students how to analyze a company's fundamentals and make informed investment decisions.

fields.title: Technical Analysis
fields.description: In this module, students learn how to use technical analysis for stock trading, including how to read stock charts and use technical indicators.

fields.title: Origami Masterclass
fields.description: This course provides a comprehensive guide to origami, the traditional Japanese art of paper folding. Students will learn basic techniques and create a variety of shapes and figures. Suitable for beginners as well as intermediate students.

fields.title: Origami Basics
fields.description: This module introduces the basic folds and techniques used in origami.

fields.title: Animals and Birds
fields.description: Learn to create origami animals and birds in this module.

fields.title: Flowers and Trees
fields.description: This module focuses on creating origami flowers and trees.

fields.title: Advanced Origami Figures
fields.description: In this module, students will be taught to create advanced figures like dragons and complex structures.
